The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Lokuarachchi to replace Muralidharan
London: Sri Lankas Muttiah Muralidharan will be replaced by Kaushal Lokuarachchi in Sri Lankas squad for next months ICC Champions Trophy in England, the ICC said on Friday. Off-spinner Muralidharan is out for five months after undergoing shoulder surgery last week. The West Indies have drafted allrounder Darren Sammy into their squad for the tournament. Sammy replaces fast bowler Jermaine Lawson, who has withdrawn due to injury, the West Indies Cricket Board said in a statement. Bangladesh captain Habibul Bashar, who is out with an injured thumb, will be replaced by Faisal Hossain. Kenyas request to replace Maurice Odumbe with Brijal Patel on exceptional grounds has also been approved by the ICC. Meanwhile, the ICC has said it would be ruthless in guarding against ambush marketing activities during the Champions Trophy. ICC chief executive Malcolm Speed said the the world body and tournament hosts, the ECB, would be guarding carefully against products being brought into any of the tournaments three grounds being used to create exposure or profile for an organisation that is not a partner of the ICC. (REUTERS)  Copyright 
